ependency is truly necessary for effective testing.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Deciding on testing setup**\\n\\nI'm considering if using the testkit is necessary for meaningful actor testing according to the docs. The extra dependencies should ideally only be added with concrete evidence. Maybe in the Forge workflow, including the recommended test dependency will help. I also notice the issue with \\\"java run fails\\\" related to compilation errors. I should guide against using the removed TypedActor APIs. So, I need to decide between no_action and advisory_preparation for the agent_guidance field regarding test-code setup.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Evaluating setup needs and risks**\\n\\nI don't see any extra setup required, but I should consider mentioning the risks associated with the removed TypedActor and the JDK's add-exports. The current build already includes JVM arguments for DnsSettings. If generated tests need to access sun.net.dns with DnsSettings, they must correctly set the module exports. I'll need to decide if that's an environment or system property. Since existing tests have already set the --add-exports for DnsSettingsTest, I should clarify that if the generator interacts with DnsSettings.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_DiJpyzSI6lPljw6hKR5osaNp|fc_057755bd348b6a33016a40d444eaac8190b6ecfbba1c1ba8e4", "name": "read", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/org.apache.pekko/pekko-actor_2.13/1.1.5/src/test/scala/org_apache_pekko/pekko_actor_2_13/VirtualThreadSupportTest.scala", "limit": 160}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 1555, "output": 713, "cacheRead": 17920, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 20188, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1782633529601, "responseId": "resp_057755bd348b6a33016a40d43a12c08190aa176dade7b4c611"}}
